    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-07-22T18:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-07-22T18:45:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <head>378. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission to the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d378fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 301, Agency Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, Vol. VII. Secret; Nodis.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1971-07-22T23:45:00+00:00">July 22, 1971, 2345Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1993. Subj: <gloss target="#t_CHIR1">Chirep</gloss>—<persName corresp="#p_BGHW1"
                        >Bush</persName>–<gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> Meeting July 22.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Summary. <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName>, during call on
                            <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> on another subject July 22, took
                        occasion to brief <persName corresp="#p_TU1">U Thant</persName> along lines
                        para 4, State 131353.<note n="2" xml:id="d378fn2">Dated July 20. (Ibid., RG
                            59, Central Files 1970–73, <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> 6 <gloss
                                target="#t_CHIC1">CHICOM</gloss>)</note>
                        <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> expressed appreciation. End
                        summary.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName> explained restrictions placed
                        on members of administration on this subject. Although US tactics in <gloss
                            target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> not yet decided and he under firm
                        instructions not to speculate, <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName>
                        said he believed he owed <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> as much
                        information as was currently available.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Basic purpose of President’s July 15 announcement was to improve relations
                        with <gloss target="#t_PRC1">PRC</gloss>. At same time, US was going to
                        continue to have good relations with <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>.
                        Our basic defense treaty will remain in force and we will work for retention
                        of <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> in the <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                            >UN</gloss>. Our assessment is that if we continued with same policy as
                        in past we would not be successful in blocking Albanian Resolution or
                        getting majority for <gloss target="#t_IQ1">IQ</gloss>. Reiterating US
                        support for <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName> said US will support <gloss
                            target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>
                        <pb facs="0772" n="735" xml:id="pg_735"/> membership in <gloss
                            target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> and noted our tactical position still being
                        worked out. Only thing yet decided is that we will vote against expulsion of
                            <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TU1">U Thant</persName> said he understood situation
                        and expressed appreciation for briefing. In reply to question, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName> said we had been in touch with WE
                        allies and others on this issue.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>In reply to <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName>’s question,
                            <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> said it possible Albanian <gloss
                            target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> cosponsors would seek and obtain priority
                        consideration in plenary immediately after general debate. This could lead
                        to question being decided about middle of October. <gloss target="#t_SYG1"
                            >SYG</gloss> volunteered, “I will then have to get in touch with
                        Peking.”</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Comment</hi>. This is first hint we have had <gloss
                            target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> may have changed his long-standing
                        prediction <gloss target="#t_PRC1">PRC</gloss> will not enter <gloss
                            target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> until Nov 1972.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Bush</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
